            <div type="translation">
                <p>Although the ogham letters are clear, apart from the very last letter(s), an exact meaning has not been determined.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
<p>The ogham inscription and the symbols can be considered contemporary (Forsyth 1996, 13). The symbols are placed slightly to the right to allow for the ogham and the carving technique employed is the same for both (ibid).</p>
<p>The inscription likely consists of a personal name and Forsyth provides an analysis of the possibilities (Forsyth 1996, 17-20).</p>
            </div>
